The paper discusses biologically plausible learning algorithms for neural networks, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). The paper also evaluates the performance of these algorithms on large datasets, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of different network architectures, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computation and Language (cs.CL).
